{"id":"228568491_1_The_Discretizable_Molecular_Distance_Geometry_Problem","abstract":"Given a simple weighted undirected graph G=(V,E,d) with d:E→ℝ+, the Molecular Distance Geometry Problem (MDGP) consists in finding an embedding x:V→ℝ3 such that ‖x\n\nu\n−x\n\nv\n‖=d\n\nuv\nfor each {u,v}∈E. We show that under a few assumptions usually satisfied in proteins, the MDGP can be formulated as a search in a discrete space. We call this MDGP subclass the Discretizable MDGP (DMDGP). We show that the DMDGP is NP-hard and we propose a solution algorithm called Branch-and-Prune (BP). The BP algorithm performs remarkably well in practice in terms of speed and solution accuracy, and can be easily modified to find all incongruent solutions to a given DMDGP instance. We show computational results on several artificial and real-life instances.","authors":["Carlile Lavor","Leo Liberti","Nelson Maculan","Antonio Mucherino"],"meta":["June 2012Computational Optimization and Applications 219(3)","DOI:10.1016/j.ejor.2011.11.007"],"references":["268018683_Distance_Geometry_and_Molecular_Conformation","265352321_Explicit_Sensor_Network_Localization_using_Semidefinite_Representations_and_Facial_Reductions","257121292_Semidefinite_Facial_Reduction_for_Low-Rank_Euclidean_Distance_Matrix_Completion","245973187_Double_VNS_for_the_Molecular_Distance_Geometry_Problem","244235393_Grover's_Algorithm_applied_to_the_Molecular_Distance_Geometry_Problem","242314200_On_the_Definition_of_Artificial_Backbones_for_the_Discretizable_Molecular_Distance_Geometry_Problem","239667563_Molecular_Modeling_and_Simulation_An_Interdisciplinary_Guide","228665757_On_the_solution_of_molecular_distance_geometry_problems_with_interval_data","228609309_An_overview_of_distinct_approaches_for_the_molecular_distance_geometry_problem","228571561_The_iBP_algorithm_for_the_discretizable_molecular_distance_geometry_problem_with_interval_data","228532123_On_Suitable_Parallel_Implementations_of_the_Branch_Prune_Algorithm_for_Dista